## Frequently Asked Questions
How does the onboarding work?
A 15 min complimentary call with a mentor or an Excellence instructor, even for the essential program. During the meeting we'll learn about your child's needs and current level to craft a highly personalized learning experience.
Is Excellence suited to my child?
Excellence is adaptative at its core, and works extremely well for 95% of children. We help students express their full potential regardless of their classroom performance, i.e we are not a program only for the top 1% learners. If your child has special needs, please mention it during the onboarding call so we can accommodate them.
The program is too expensive, what can I do?
We believe every child deserves the chance to excel. That’s why we offer scholarships—both merit-based and need-based—for motivated students whose parents need assistance. Simply start your trial, mention your request during the 15-minute onboarding call, and we’ll review your application within 24 hours.To further support families, we provide a 50% discount for additional children. If you're not in the United States, further discounts may apply. 
[Request discount](https://excellence-ai.com/<https:/app.excellence-ai.com/book-call>)
How much time does my child need for this program?
Consistency is the secret. We suggest beginning with 10 minutes per day, which already yields exceptional results in a 3-6 months timeframe. Excellence's software gauges your child's motivation on a daily basis, and, if you chose the mentorship plan, the mentor will do the same. As soon as your child is ready for more—or less, we'll suggest a change. Children can also ask for an amendment directly.Motivated students devote up to 30 minutes per day, get several years ahead and acquire exceptional skills in mathematics and science.
I already have a tutor, is Excellence still for me?
Absolutely! It has been incredibly effective for our customers. In our experience, tutors primarily address students' immediate needs—homework, exams, and school-related questions. However, unless a student has a tutor every day, their progress remains reactive rather than proactive. Excellence takes learning to a whole new level by systematically building your child’s math skills for long-term success, fostering independence and confidence. In short, Excellence doesn’t replace a tutor—it makes one unnecessary within 1 to 2 years.
Is Excellence’s platform aligned with what my child learns at school?
It is— meaning what they learn will translate into higher grades and a deeper understanding of what they do at school. However our program is long-term focused, so we won't necessarily teach everything in te exact same way. In fact, our handcrafted curriculum allows for a much faster, more in-depth learning than Common Core, and will allow your child to skip ahead. In addition of the program, we provide a cutting-edge AI tutor to help your child work on school materials and prepare for exams.
My child likes to do maths on paper, is that something you accommodate?
Absolutely, we cater to both paper and digital learners, and can even mail courses and exercices weekly to your home— for free.
I am passionate about STEM education and technology, how can get involved ?
Contact us at founders@excellence-ai.com. We'd love to hear from you.
